      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the FDA-accepted metric for comparative hemolysis assessment of CPB devices. RH directly quantifies hemolysis relative to the predicate device and maps to the clinical endpoint of hemolysis-related patient harm. The QoI is fully relevant to the COU decision."
